//~~
//~~ The jewel upgrade system can convert defined items/options to completely new item, options or both.
//~~ Example, you can upgrade Leather Armor to Dragon Armor with the jewel or give new properties to existing item.
//~~ Supported jewels 19,210~240
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem ###
//	Enable: Deactivates or activates the system, 0/1
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::IgnoreItemList::Item ###
//	Cat: Category of item to ignore
//	Index: Index of item to ignore
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::Jewel ###
//	Cat: Category of jewel item, always 19
//	Index: Index of jewel item, 210-240
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//~~ Every jewel type can be defined once only, however item defined under specific
//~~ jewel can be configured multiple times using different matching rules
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// ### JewelUpgradeSystem::Jewel::Item
//	Type: Type of item to match, see ItemList.xml Type attribute, -1 to ignore
//	KindA: Kind A of item to match, see ItemList.xml KindA attribute, -1 to ignore
//	KindB: Kind B of item to match, see ItemList.xml KindB attribute, -1 to ignore
//	Cat: Category of item to upgrade
//	Index: Index of item to upgrade
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//~~ If Cat and Index are both set to -1 then will be ignored
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
//	MinLevel: Minimum level of item to upgrade, 0-15
//	MaxLevel: Maximum level of item to upgrade, 0-15
//	MinExcOpt: Minimum number of excellent options on the item
//	MaxExcOpt: Maximum number of excellent options on the item
//	SetItem:
//		~ -1: ignores the set item check
//		~ 0: cannot be a set item
//		~ 1: must be a set item
//
//	Success: Success rate of upgrade, n/100
//	RewardCat: Category of upgrade result item, if set to -1 then rewarded item is automatically set to cat/index of source item
//	RewardIndex: Index of upgrade result item
//	RewardLevel: Level of upgrade result item, 0-15
//	RewardItemDurability: Durability of reward item, -1 to set automatically
//	FailPenalty: In case of failure, different kind of penalties may be applied:
//		~ -1: No penalty
//		~ 0: Destroy item
//		~ 1-15: Reduce item level by random number up to defined value
//
//	RewardSetItem: Rewards ancient version of the item (if available), 0/1
//	RewardExc: Number of new excellent options that will be added to existing ones, supports wings
//	RewardSocket: Number of socket slots that will be added to existing ones
//		~ -2: random count of socket slots (Pentagrams only)
//		~ 0-5: specific number of sockets
//
//	ElementalItem (Pentagrams and Errtels only):
//		~ 0: no Elemental attribute
//		~ 1: Fire
//		~ 2: Water
//		~ 3: Earth
//		~ 4: Wind
//		~ 5: Darkness
//		~ -1: Random attribute
//
// STRICTLY NO COMMENTS INSIDE TAGS
-->

